-- Sacyr Gets $78 Million Contract to Build Two Peru Hydro Projects
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-06-12T13:58:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-12/sacyr-gets-78-million-contract-to-build-two-peru-hydro-projects.html
Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV) , the Spanish
construction company, won a 59 million-euro ($78.4 million)
contract to build two hydroelectric power plants in Peru.  The projects will be built for Generacion Andina SAC and
have total capacity of 28.4 megawatts, Madrid-based Sacyr said
today on its  website . The 8 de Agosto plant and the El Carmen
facility are both planned for the Huanuco region in central
Peru.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
